{
  "texts": [
    "Outside the analogy, other factors than the speedup are likely needed to be taken into account to judge if practical quantum advantage has occurred.",
    "Qualitybased generalization is one of these playgrounds.",
    "This is particularly relevant when considering combinatorial optimization problems, as suggested by the generative enhanced optimization (GEO) framework 38.",
    "This reference introduces a connection between generative models and optimization, which is in and of itself a new perspective on a family of commercially valuable use cases for generative models beyond large language models and image generation, but that is not fully appreciated yet by the ML community.",
    "Remarkably, quality-based generalization turns out to be paramount when the generative modeling task under examination is linked to a cost-equipped optimization problem."
  ]
}